quizzes.textContent:
[h1]String Concatenation[/h1]

The + (plus) operator between strings adds them together to make a new string. This process is called [b]concatenation[/b].
The resulted string is the first string put together with the second string.
For example: [code format="java" codeId="726"][b]String[/b] firstName, lastName;
firstName = "David";
lastName = "Williams";

System.out.println("My name is " + firstName +" "+lastName);
        
// Prints: My name is David Williams[/code]
[note]The [b]char [/b]data type represents a single character. [/note]
